# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Git - Commit — GitHub OAuth Configuration
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# 1. Go to https://github.com/settings/developers
# 2. Click "OAuth Apps" → "New OAuth App"
# 3. Fill in:
#    - Application name: Git - Commit
#    - Homepage URL: http://localhost:8371
#    - Authorization callback URL: http://localhost:8371/auth/callback
# 4. Click "Register application"
# 5. Copy Client ID below
# 6. Click "Generate a new client secret" and copy below
# 7. Rename this file to .env
#
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=your_client_id_here
GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET=your_client_secret_here
